Last year I swapped over to this aftermarket rear fender for Caroline. Unfortunately it’s been a letdown as the plastic has already cracked apart, the signals/break light aren’t strong enough, it negates a few factory parts that keep the battery and electronics snug under the seat, and it creates a wonky gap between frame and seat. With all that said I chopped down the original and will move back to the lights I last used. Heading to paint soon and she’ll be good to go!

(I know my shop is a mess. It’s still winter here, which means spring cleaning hasn’t taken place.)
New Hacksaw goods! We just dropped baseball jerseys and tote bags – I’ll be proudly donning mine as prada gets back on tour in a little bit. Shop now, folks.

TDWP is auctioning off nineteen items with all proceeds to benefit the American Foundation for Suicide Prevention. Proud of @mason.nagy.71 for initializing and spearheading this effort, to say the very least. Auctions end tomorrow, link in @tdwpband bio!
Here’s the back half of the video i made and posted a couple weeks ago. Off to paint this evening! I’ll have lights done and ready to ride following the upcoming TDWP tour.
Popped a standard @lollarpickups Imperial in the bridge of the workhorse a few months ago but then the neck went out. Bad connections at the toggle. The masterful @nateball has her back to 100%

See below:

Too excited to unbox my new EGC to brush post-skate hockey hair. Series 5 with TB HBs, acid dip body and black anodize neck. Dream custom. Thank you so much to Kevin and the team - more details on @electricalguitarcompany IG.

Following up on some reels earlier this year, my chopped fender returned from paint perfect, and i went back to the first set of rear lighting i came up with for Caroline. I am pleased. My shop is still messy.

When i remodeled the kitchen i popped the old cabinets in the garage for my miter station, and it’s long been since due to upgrade what I’ve got going. Next I’ll finish drawers and add a @rockler_woodworking t-track for precise measuring.

I am excited to participate in the Pucks for Autism tournament later this month! if you’d like to help raise funds for an excellent cause, check my linktree and make a donation. We also have @pucksforautism collaborative tees in the @hacksawhockey store with all proceeds to PFA!
It’s been a couple years, but my Etsy shop is coming back! Stay tuned.

Never shared a pic since the rear fender mod. Also new turn signals up front, mounted mirror underbar, and removed front fender.
Etsy! I’m back selling small stools/stands. I hope to create a bunch more before prada touring resumes, all the same seven available offerings are live. Link in my linktree.
I’ve been through a lot with Old Blue. It’s been a few years since i had her rideable, but she’s back and it’s been fun.

Busy day! Brand new website is live, which includes fresh pressings of Bullet-Made Tambourine and Home for Grave (with a ten year anniversary foreword). Both will be available at merch if you’re coming to a TDWP gig (hi @juanpardo.png). Tour starts tonight! Dates -> @tdwpband 
Thanks for the quick pic @imanigivertz

Dogma is closing its doors – while my buddy Micah and i created the brand with highest expectations, it hasn’t panned out as we planned, nor have either of us found the time. Prices are marked way down on merchandise, plus of course last batches of beans. Visit dogmacoffee.com
A favorite detail. We got insanely lucky to be giggin’ Charlotte same day as @thecongregationshow // super, super rad. Sold out tonight, sold out tomorrow in Atlanta. All dates and tickets @tdwpband
